cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new neural architecture for end-to-end speech recognition, which falls under the domain of natural language processing. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is also a likely category as the paper deals with speech recognition, which involves processing of audio signals. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper proposes a new neural architecture that reduces the number of parameters and boosts the speed in training and inference for speech recognition. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper proposes a new neural architecture for speech recognition, which is a subfield of AI. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with optimizing the performance of a neural network for speech recognition, which can be seen as a control problem.
